# Portfolio Design System Rules

Apply these rules whenever editing `index.html` or `about.html`.

---

## 1. Always Use CSS Custom Properties

**Never write a raw hex or rgb value in a `<style>` block.** Use the token.

### Semantic color tokens

| Token | Dark | Light | Role |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--color-bg` | `#0e0b09` | `#f6f4ff` | Page background |
| `--color-text` | `#faf3e3` | `#120f2a` | Primary text and icon color |
| `--color-surface` | `#161210` | `#ebe7ff` | Card / elevated surface background |
| `--color-primary` | `#9b8fff` | `#4e42d0` | Brand accent — headings, links, active states, focus rings |
| `--color-accent` | `#82e785` | `#1e9248` | CTA-only accent — filled button background |
| `--color-muted` | `#5c5048` | `#6e67a8` | Toggle thumb, secondary borders, decorative UI |
| `--color-border` | `#1d1a16` | `#cdc8f0` | Dividers, card borders |

> ⚠️ Light-mode primary is `#4e42d0`. The old value `#6b5fe8` failed WCAG AA contrast (~4.4:1). Do NOT revert it.

### Tonal color scale

When a semantic token is too heavy or too light, pick the nearest tonal step. **Always prefer a semantic token first; use tonal steps only when a deliberate shade variation is needed.**

**Primary (purple)**

| Token | Dark | Light |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-primary-100` | `#e8e5ff` | `#e8e5ff` |
| `--color-primary-300` | `#c4bcff` | `#9b8fff` |
| `--color-primary-500` | `#9b8fff` | `#6b5fe8` |
| `--color-primary-700` | `#6b5fe8` | `#4e42d0` |
| `--color-primary-900` | `#3d31b0` | `#2f2597` |

**Accent (green)**

| Token | Dark | Light |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-accent-100` | `#d4f5d5` | `#d4f5d5` |
| `--color-accent-300` | `#82e785` | `#4fcf57` |
| `--color-accent-500` | `#52c758` | `#1e9248` |
| `--color-accent-700` | `#3aaa40` | `#156832` |
| `--color-accent-900` | `#1e6b22` | `#0d4116` |

**Permitted hardcoded values (narrow exceptions):**
- `color: #1d1d1d` on `.contact-btn` — fixed dark text on bright green accent, no suitable token
- `fill="…"` attributes inside `<svg>` elements that represent brand decorations (vinyl labels, pixel art)

### Typography tokens

| Token | Value |
|---|---|
| `--font-sans` | `'Work Sans', system-ui, sans-serif` |
| `--font-serif` | `'Fraunces', Georgia, serif` |
| `--font-mono` | `'DM Mono', 'Courier New', monospace` |
| `--serif-display` | `'SOFT' 0, 'WONK' 1` (font-variation-settings for Fraunces) |

---

## 2. Font Assignment Rule

| If the text is… | Use |
|---|---|
| `text-transform: uppercase` | `var(--font-mono)` — always, no exceptions |
| A heading, display line, or italic decorative text | `var(--font-serif)` + `font-variation-settings: var(--serif-display)` |
| Body copy, UI labels that are NOT uppercase, meta text | `var(--font-sans)` |

### Mono tracking rule

All mono / uppercase UI text uses **0px letter-spacing** (no tracking).

---

## 3. Opacity Floors

Do not set opacity below these values on text-bearing elements:

| Element type | Minimum opacity |
|---|---|
| Running body paragraphs | `0.78` |
| UI labels, muted text, toggle labels, footer | `0.65` |
| Decorative image labels (on dark gradient overlay only) | `0.45` |
| **Nothing text-bearing goes below `0.45`** | |

---

## 4. Font Size Minimums

| Context | Minimum |
|---|---|
| All UI text | `11px` |
| Decorative image labels (on dark overlay) | `10px` — only this exception |

Do not introduce new text elements smaller than `11px`.

---

## 5. Every New Interactive Element Needs a Focus Style

Any new `<a>`, `<button>`, or focusable element must include:

```css
.element:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
  outline-offset: 2px;     /* 3–4px for block rows, 2px for inline */
  border-radius: 2px;
}
```

Exception: `.contact-btn` uses `var(--color-text)` for the outline because the accent background needs higher-contrast focus ring.

---

## 6. Entrance Animations Need a Reduced-Motion Override

If you add a new element that starts hidden with `opacity: 0` and animates in, you must add an override in the existing `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` block:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .new-element {
    opacity: 1;       /* or the final resting opacity */
    transform: none;
    animation: none;
  }
}
```

The grain SVG animation (`grain-drift`) must also remain suppressed in that block.

---

## 7. Theme Token Consistency

Color tokens must be defined in three places and kept in sync:

1. `:root` (dark default)
2. `@media (prefers-color-scheme: light) :root`
3. `[data-theme="light"]` and `[data-theme="dark"]` explicit selectors

This applies to **both** semantic tokens and tonal scale tokens. When editing a token value, update all four occurrences (both HTML files share the same token set and must stay identical).

---

## 8. Theme Hierarchy

**Dark and light are the primary themes.** All design changes apply to them first.

**Fun (`data-theme="fun"`) is a supplemental theme.** Unless a change is explicitly labelled "fun only":
- Apply the change to dark and light only.
- Exception: if you change `--color-primary`, `--color-accent`, or either tonal scale, also update the inverted mapping in `[data-theme="fun"]` to keep it correct.
- Fun-only changes touch only `[data-theme="fun"]` and its scoped rules — never the dark/light blocks.

